Hi,

Thanks for writing to Dr. Math.

You can use a logarithm. If a and b are constants and x is a variable:

   a^x = b

Then:

   log(a^x) = log(b)

   x*log(a) = log(b)

          x = log(b)/log(a)

Does this help?  Please feel free to write back with any questions you
may have.

- Doctor Roy, The Math Forum
